Module io.jstach.rainbowgum
Package io.jstach.rainbowgum

Interface LogAppender

All Superinterfaces:
AutoCloseable, LogLifecycle
public sealed interface LogAppender extends LogLifecycle
Appenders are guaranteed to be written synchronously much like an actor in actor concurrency. They safely hold onto and communicate with the encoder and output. Appenders largely deal with correct locking, buffer reuse and flushing. Flags can be set to control the behavior the appenders and publishers can request different appender behavior through the flags.
See Also:
  • LogAppender.AppenderFlag
API Note
because appenders require complicated implementation and to guarantee integrity the implementations are encapsulated (sealed).
